just_use extract_longest_program.py

# label: TOOL (OPTIMIZE_PYTHON era)
# role: dump the longest DSL-style program a runaway projection produces

For a given runaway evil card, walks the BFS up to the
state cap and prints the longest candidate program as
numbered describe_move(desc) lines. Useful for inspecting
"what is the agent chasing" qualitatively.

Steve uses these to look for structural patterns —
duplicate twins, excessive sacrifice chains, doomed
intermediate states — that drove the cap exhaustion.

```
python3 extract_longest_program.py /tmp/runaway_hunt.jsonl \
    --evil "10/0/0" --max-states 5000
```

## Pointers

- `runaway_puzzles.py` — posts each runaway as a puzzle.
- `agent_game.py --offline --capture` — produces the
  source JSONL.
